data.title: Newell Brands (NASDAQ: NWL) reports Q3 2025 financial results despite trade disruptions. CEO states sales were affected.
data.description: In Atlanta, Newell Brands (NASDAQ: NWL) revealed its financial results for the third quarter of 2025. Chris Peterson, President and CEO of Newell Brands, emphasized the progress of their turnaround despite facing trade disruptions during the quarter. The company quickly implemented strategic measures such as sourcing alterations, pricing adjustments, and productivity enhancements to counter the challenges. Sales figures were impacted by these disruptions.

data.title: Kuick Research predicts global multispecific antibody market to surpass USD 50 billion by 2030 with sales over USD 12 billion in 2024. 700+ antibodies in clinical trials show exciting M&A opportunities. More info at: https://www.kuickresearch.com/report-multispecific-antibodies-market
data.description: Kuick Research has released a Global Multispecific Antibodies Market Report aimed at investors and corporate development teams, highlighting the potential of this rapidly advancing biotechnology sector. The report provides insights on the market opportunity, with projections of over USD 50 billion by 2030 and sales exceeding USD 12 billion in 2024. Currently, there are 18 approved multispecific antibodies, with over 700 in various stages of clinical trials worldwide. These antibodies are revolutionizing therapeutic strategies in oncology, hematology, and autoimmune diseases, attracting investment opportunities for both established pharmaceutical companies and emerging biotech firms. The full story is available on Benzinga.com.

data.title: Empowering children with disabilities in Central African Republic to access inclusive education by Education Cannot Wait, UNICEF, and partners.
data.description: In the region of Bambari in the Central African Republic, Education Cannot Wait, along with UNICEF and their collaborators, are working towards providing children with disabilities the opportunity to receive inclusive education and achieve their maximum capabilities. Taking place in the town of Bambari, the project aims to improve educational access for these children. The initiative, launched on October 31, 2025, is crucial for empowering children in the area.

data.title: Motive partners with a Central/South American operator to bring seamless eSIM activation to luxury car brand in Mexico.
data.description: Motive, a renowned company specializing in connected device lifecycle management and automation, has recently revealed a significant collaboration with a prominent telecommunications provider in Central and South America. This partnership aims to deliver smooth and secure mobile connectivity services to the vehicles of a prestigious European automotive brand in Mexico. The innovative solution relies on Motive's Entitlement Server technology, which allows the operator's customers to easily connect their mobile accounts with their vehicles through embedded SIM (eSIM) technology.

data.title: Advanced Energy declares quarterly dividend of $0.10 per share, payable on December 5, 2025 to shareholders of record on November 24, 2025.
data.description: Denver-based company Advanced Energy Industries, Inc. (NASDAQ: AEIS), known for its precision power conversion solutions, declared a quarterly cash dividend of $0.10 per share. This dividend will be paid on December 5, 2025, to shareholders holding stocks as of November 24, 2025. The board of directors will review and approve future dividend declarations and determine the record and payment dates for upcoming dividends.

data.title: Third Quarter 2025 financial results: Protolabs revenue hits $135.4 million, up 7.8% from Q3 2024. Digital factory revenue at $105.3 million, up 4.9%.
data.description: In Minneapolis, Proto Labs, Inc., a top digital manufacturing services provider, revealed its financial performance for the quarter ending September 30, 2025. The company, listed on the NYSE as PRLB, reported record revenue of $135.4 million, marking a 7.8% rise from $125.6 million in the same period last year. Of this revenue, $105.3 million came from digital factories, reflecting a 4.9% increase from the previous year. These results underline Proto Labs’ continued growth and success in the digital manufacturing sector.

data.title: Albert Invent sponsors 2025 GDCh Annual Member Meeting in Frankfurt, deepening European presence.
data.description: Albert Invent, a company based in Frankfurt am Main, Germany, has revealed its sponsorship of the Gesellschaft Deutscher Chemiker (GDCh) Annual Member Meeting scheduled for November 13–14, 2025. The event, organized by VCW, a division of GDCh concentrating on the economics and commercialization of chemical research, will explore the influence of technological advancements on the industry. Albert Invent's AI-driven platform that is revolutionizing R&D in the chemical and materials sectors will be showcased at the conference.

data.title: Flowco Holdings Inc. (NYSE: FLOC) declares $0.08 quarterly cash dividend for Class A common stockholders on Nov 26, 2025.
data.description: Houston-based Flowco Holdings Inc. (NYSE: FLOC) revealed a cash dividend of $0.08 per share of Class A common stock. This dividend is set to be paid on November 26, 2025, to Class A common stockholders of record as of November 14, 2025. Specializing in production optimization, artificial lift, and methane abatement solutions for the oil and natural gas sector, Flowco operates through its subsidiary, Flowco MergeCo LLC.

data.title: Issuer of Trump Memecoin in talks to buy Republic, aiming to boost startup funding. Controversy swirls as CZ's pardon stirs up political tensions.
data.description: Fight Fight Fight LLC, the creator of the Trump memecoin, is currently negotiating the acquisition of Republic.com’s operations in the United States. This move aims to incorporate the token into their startup crowdfunding endeavors. The decision comes in the midst of political controversies surrounding CZ's pardon.

data.title: Positive long-term data for BT-101 treatment of Osteogenesis imperfecta revealed at conference, with two-year follow-up data from BOOSTB4 trial. Karolinska Development's portfolio company, BOOST Pharma, showed promising results at the 15th International Conference on OI in Hong Kong.
data.description: In Stockholm, Sweden on October 31, 2025, Karolinska Development AB revealed that its portfolio company BOOST Pharma has shared updated long-term data from the BOOSTB4 phase 1/2 trial showcasing the performance of the cell therapy BT-101 aimed at treating the uncommon bone ailment Osteogenesis imperfecta. The data includes a two-year follow-up from the trial and was displayed at the esteemed 15th International Conference on Osteogenesis imperfecta in Hong Kong held from October 29 to 31.BOOST Pharma's cell therapy BT-101 targets Osteogenesis imperfecta, which is a rare bone disease.
